{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C.","Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a jug and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place sugar, eggs, orange zest and salt into mixing bowl and beat <b>4 min\/speed 4<b>. Meanwhile, use approx. 1 tablespoon of the melted butter and a pastry brush to grease a 12-hole madeleine tray, then dust with flour, shaking out any excess. Set aside."," <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and remaining melted butter and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <b>3 sec\/speed 3<b> or until just combined. Divide mixture between madeleine moulds and bake for 8-10 minutes (170°C) or until madeleines spring back when lightly pressed in the centre. Remove from oven, cool in the tin for 2 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely. Dust with icing sugar to serve (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g unsalted butter, softened and cut into pieces","60 g caster sugar","2 eggs","1 orange, zest only, no white pith","1 pinch salt","60 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","1 tbsp cocoa powder","1 tsp baking powder","icing sugar, for dusting (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r250029","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-PvwdEbakFC0\/XZWpsSMpcGI\/AAAAAAAAfNk\/woQ36sG9DxY3c6J34Si2G2n5D1DML9SWACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2LZgpUIHUOG5JtDJ.png","title":"Jaffa madeleines","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.9 g","fat":"7.7 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"10.6 g","calories":"495.6 kJ \/ 118 kcal"},"usefulItems":"madeleine tray, wire rack, jug, pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own icing sugar, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","Madeleines are best eaten on the day they are made."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","12 portions"]}